      • DatabaseParameterSet

      • DatabaseParameterSet

        public DatabaseParameterSet(java.lang.String[] attributeNames,
                            int[] keyColumns,
                            java.lang.String rowItemLabel)
        This constructor is used when the set contains a large number of rows. Sending a large number of rows to a Pebbles list view in an array is not efficient. Instead, supplying these fields will cause the Pebbles page to display the data with a ToolbarRangeInput dropdown, labelled with the rowItemLabel, and populated with the values from the columns supplied in keyColumns. For example, if the table and index are in columns 0 and 1 of the attribute values array, then keyColumns would be {0,1}.
        Parameters:
        attributeNames - names of attributes
        keyColumns - key columns
        rowItemLabel - label of row item
